# File: tests/features/vault-rag.feature
#
# Generated from: specs/feature-rag-prompt-injection/requirements.md
# Issue: #10

Feature: RAG prompt injection hook
  As a Claude Code + Obsidian user working across many projects
  I want relevant prior notes from my vault surfaced automatically on every prompt
  So that Claude answers with continuity from past sessions without manual copy-paste

  Background:
    Given a scratch HOME at "$BATS_TEST_TMPDIR/home"
    And a scratch Obsidian vault at "$BATS_TEST_TMPDIR/vault"
    And obsidian-memory is installed and setup against "$VAULT"

  # --- Happy Path ---

  Scenario: A vault note contains a keyword from the prompt
    Given a vault file "my-note.md" containing "jq is used for config parsing"
    When the user submits a prompt containing "How do I use jq for config parsing?"
    Then the hook stdout contains a "<vault-context source=\"obsidian\"" opening tag
    And the block contains the relative path "my-note.md"
    And the block contains the excerpt text "jq is used for config parsing"
    And the block closes with "</vault-context>"
    And the hook exit code is 0

  Scenario: Top-5 ranking and excerpt format
    Given 10 vault notes each matching the prompt with a known hit count
    When the hook runs against a prompt matching the shared keyword
    Then the "<vault-context>" block lists exactly 5 notes
    And the notes are ordered by descending hit count
    And each listed note has a "### <rel-path>  (hits: <N>)" header
    And each excerpt is fenced in triple-backticks
    And each excerpt is no more than 600 bytes

  # --- Happy Path — silent ---

  Scenario: No matching notes
    Given a vault whose ".md" files contain no prompt keywords
    When the user submits a prompt with no overlapping tokens
    Then the hook emits no "<vault-context>" block
    And the hook exit code is 0

  # --- Alternative Paths ---

  Scenario: "rg" is not on PATH — POSIX fallback
    Given "rg" is unavailable in the hook subshell
    And a vault file "my-note.md" contains the text "ripgrep not needed"
    When the user submits a prompt containing "ripgrep"
    Then the hook still emits a "<vault-context>" block for "my-note.md"
    And scoring used "grep -c -i -E" rather than "rg -c"
    And the hook exit code is 0

  Scenario: RAG disabled via config
    Given the config file has "rag.enabled" set to false
    When the user submits any prompt
    Then the hook emits no output on stdout
    And the hook did not enumerate files under "$VAULT"
    And the hook exit code is 0

  # --- Edge Cases — exclusion list ---

  Scenario: Auto-memory projects symlink is excluded
    Given "$VAULT/claude-memory/projects/some-project/2026-04-18.jsonl" contains "jq"
    And no other file in "$VAULT" contains "jq"
    When the user submits a prompt containing "jq"
    Then the hook emits no "<vault-context>" block
    And the hook exit code is 0

  Scenario: Obsidian metadata directories are excluded
    Given "$VAULT/.obsidian/workspace.json" contains the prompt keyword
    And "$VAULT/.trash/deleted-note.md" contains the prompt keyword
    And no other file contains the keyword
    When the user submits a matching prompt
    Then the hook emits no "<vault-context>" block
    And the hook exit code is 0

  # --- Error Handling — silent ---

  Scenario: Missing jq dependency
    Given "jq" is unavailable in the hook subshell
    When the user submits any prompt
    Then the hook emits no output on stdout
    And the hook exit code is 0

  Scenario: Missing config file
    Given "$HOME/.claude/obsidian-memory/config.json" does not exist
    When the user submits any prompt
    Then the hook emits no output on stdout
    And the hook exit code is 0

  # --- Edge Cases — tokenizer ---

  Scenario: Stopwords are filtered
    Given a vault with arbitrary content
    When the user submits a prompt that contains only stopwords
    Then the hook emits no "<vault-context>" block
    And the hook exit code is 0

  Scenario: Keyword cap of 6 is enforced
    Given a prompt containing 20 distinct non-stopword tokens of length >= 4
    When the hook tokenizes the prompt
    Then the alternation regex contains at most 6 alternatives
    And the "keywords" attribute of the "<vault-context>" block lists at most 6 tokens

  # --- Security ---

  Scenario: Prompt containing shell metacharacters is safe
    Given a vault file "note.md" containing "safe keyword test"
    When the user submits a prompt containing "$(whoami) ; rm -rf /  `echo x`  'injection' \"quote\""
    Then no subshell is spawned from prompt content
    And no "whoami" output appears in the hook output
    And the hook exits 0
    And any "<vault-context>" block contains only literal keyword text
